## Essential Lessons from the Audiobook

* Define your "finish line" before starting.
* Make progress visible.
* Use micro-actions to avoid overwhelm.
* Build a daily cadence of execution.
* Create an environment that eliminates friction.
* Use closure rituals to reinforce identity.
* Avoid novelty traps.
* Develop a No-Excuses Push List.
* Conduct After-Action Reviews.

